::Spears::

She heard Prebon's voice. She set her glass down and went to the 
bridge.  She walked in and looked at Prebon. She nodded to him and 
stood against the wall, waitng to hear what prebon had to say.  She 
also thought that is Slayer was going to give her trouble, she might 
want to stay out of his way for a while. Untill he got used to the 
idea that she was going to be around and here to stay no matter what 
Slayer thought or wanted.  She folded her arms across her chest and 
leaned against the wall.  She lowered her head and went deep into 
thought.  She wanted to tell Slayer who he was and where he had come 
from.  But prebon had ordered her not to speak a word of it to him. 
She closed her eyes and felt the chip straighten out her programs. 
She now felt like she had to focus on the mission and what Prebon 
wold order her to do.  Not worry about trivial problems like old 
friends.
